February 4th 2017
Concert Starts

at 7 p.m.&amp;nbsp;

&amp;nbsp;

Jackson Rancheria Casino Resort welcomes rock star guitarist Ace Frehley to the Grand Oak Ballroom stage.

&amp;nbsp;



As both a showman and a musician, Frehley made an impact on pop culture as a member of KISS until his successful solo career kick started in the early eighties with his smash hit &amp;ldquo;New York Groove.&amp;rdquo; Over the course of his career, Frehley has sold out concerts globally, has received a nomination into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame.

&amp;nbsp;



Will Call opens at 5 p.m., doors open at 6 p.m., and the show begins at 7 p.m.

&amp;nbsp;

Tickets are on sale now starting at $35 for Dreamcatcher&amp;rsquo;s Club&amp;reg; members, available only at the Casino Cashier&amp;rsquo;s Cage and starting at $40 for non-Dreamcatcher&amp;rsquo;s Club&amp;reg; members, available at the Casino Cashier Cage or online at JacksonCasino.com.

