3rd Saturday

of February

6:00pm

&amp;nbsp;

The Italian Society will host an all you can eat Shrimp and Chower Feed at the Society Grounds with a no host bar starting at 6:00pm followed by dinner at 7:00pm.

&amp;nbsp;

Dinner includes all you can eat shrimp, clam chower, pesto pasta, salad, bread, antipasto, desert, and wine on the table.

&amp;nbsp;

Tickets can be purchased at American River Bank in Jackson or ItalianBenevolentSociety.com.

&amp;nbsp;

Get your tickets soon as seating is limited.

&amp;nbsp;

The Italian Benevolent Society is the oldest independent Italian Society in the United States.&amp;nbsp; Established in 1881 as a charitable institution for the aid of&amp;nbsp; families of Italian Miners. These miners worked the Gold Mines of Amador County. The Society provided death benefits to those killed in the mines. As time went on it became a social and comunity based organization. The Society has been in operation for the past 130 years.

&amp;nbsp;

Italian Picnic Grounds

581 Highway 49

(Hwy 49 &amp;amp; Ridge Rd)

Sutter Hill, CA&amp;nbsp; 95685

209-267-0206

&amp;nbsp;

Take a historical flashlight tour of Preston Castle!

&amp;nbsp;

You will take&amp;nbsp; 70-90 minute tour through a 120 year old castle guided only by docent and your flashlight.&amp;nbsp; This is not a paranormal event.

&amp;nbsp;

Space is limited to 45 pre-paid guests.&amp;nbsp; Gates open a half hour before the tour.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Tour times vary based on sunset.&amp;nbsp; See times below.

Fourth Friday each month

January&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; 5:00pm

February&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; 5:30pm

March &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; 7:00pm

April&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; 7:30pm&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;

&amp;nbsp;

Dress warmly.&amp;nbsp; The castle can be very chilly especially at night.&amp;nbsp; Cost: $20.00.&amp;nbsp; No refund.

&amp;nbsp;

For more information and to order tickets visit PrestonCastleFoundation.com/FlashlightTours.

&amp;nbsp;

Preston Castle

900 Palm Dr.&amp;nbsp;(end of Palm Drive)

Ione, CA &amp;nbsp;95640

(209)256-3623

info@preston castle.com

&amp;nbsp;



Formerly Preston School of Industry, Preston Castle is a California State Historical Landmark and is listed on the National Register of Historic Places.&amp;nbsp; 

