Saturday &amp;amp; Sunday

First Weekend in March

&amp;nbsp;

Fans of Amador County wines will not be fed a steady diet of Cabernet Sauvignon, Chardonnay, Merlot and other &amp;lsquo;mainstream&amp;rsquo; varieties when they visit the historic region&amp;rsquo;s charming small family wineries. Instead, you will be treated to a cornucopia of old-vine zinfandels, syrahs, sangioveses, barberas, viogniers and other &amp;lsquo;off-the-beaten-track&amp;rsquo;, which flourish in Amador&amp;rsquo;s sun-bathed hillside vineyards. These delicious, food-friendly wines will be showcased at the Amador Vintners&amp;rsquo; annual &amp;ldquo;Behind the Cellar Door&amp;rdquo; weekend wine extravaganza.

&amp;nbsp;

The event features tastings from barrel and bottle at 39 Amador County wineries, along with a diverse array of entertainment, demonstrations, tours and seminars. Library and vertical tastings, live music, gourmet foods, numerous winemaker dinners and perhaps Sunday brunch fill out the weekend&amp;rsquo;s festivities.

&amp;nbsp;

Presale tickets are available for both days, Sunday only and reduced price for designated driver. Tickets will be available at participating wineries during the event. *Must be 21 or older to purchase.


https://www.cellarpass.com/behind-the-cellar-door-tickets-1989?p=537690


&amp;nbsp;

Amador Vintners Association

9310 Pacific Street

Plymouth, CA&amp;nbsp; 95669

(209) 245-6992&amp;nbsp; 

director@amadorwine.com

