CAPTIONS:&amp;nbsp; Example of what you&amp;rsquo;ll make in Lorra Lee Rose&amp;rsquo;s class; Jackie Martinez of Ione is a satisfied bonsai student; the class in dramatic arts is always popular at A Taste of the Arts; poster

&amp;nbsp;

Sign-Ups for &amp;ldquo;A Taste of the Arts&amp;rdquo; Begin January 30

&amp;nbsp;

Feel like it&amp;rsquo;s time to express yourself by doing a little art? But don&amp;rsquo;t know how or what&amp;rsquo;s right for you? AmadorArts is providing a way. Don&amp;rsquo;t miss the opportunity on Saturday, March 25, to take three 90-minute workshops of your choice given by some of our area&amp;rsquo;s top artists.&amp;nbsp; This seventh annual &amp;ldquo;mini arts institute&amp;rdquo; is open to residents in Amador and Calaveras Counties, or beyond, and specifically targets adults and junior and high school students.&amp;nbsp; From a menu of 19 classes, attendees may select three courses to &amp;ldquo;take a taste&amp;rdquo; of the arts, either for the first time or for further exploration. The cost for three classes, supplies included (exception: the feather classes), &amp;nbsp;is $40 for adults; $20 for junior and high school students.

Saturday

March 25, 2017

8am-2pm

&amp;nbsp;

You won&amp;rsquo;t want to miss this once-a-year opportunity to develop a &amp;quot;taste for the arts&amp;quot;!&amp;nbsp; This popular, fun mini arts institute is hosted by AmadorArts each spring at Amador High School in Sutter Creek.&amp;nbsp; 

&amp;nbsp;

Participants select three classes, each 90 minutes in length, from a menu of more than 13 classes given by some of our area&amp;rsquo;s top artists which could include anything from Watercolor and Acrylic Painting to The Art of Bonsai or Line Dancing.&amp;nbsp; 

&amp;nbsp;

Pre-Registration opens is required.&amp;nbsp; Registrations opens January 5th.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Registration closes February 19th. Check for Class Prices

&amp;nbsp;

&amp;nbsp;(all supplies are included). 

&amp;nbsp;

Classes filled first-come/first-served with a maximum of 15 students per class.&amp;nbsp;No late registrations and no refunds.

&amp;nbsp;

Amador High School

330 Spainish Street

Sutter Creek

info@amadorarts.org

(209) 267-9038

