Annually

1st Saturday in April

Check-in 7am

Race 8am sharp

&amp;nbsp;

Lace up your shoes for the Amador County Recreation Agency&amp;#39;s Annual 49er Bypass Run in downtown Sutter Creek.

&amp;nbsp;

This 5K and 10K course takes you through the rolling hills of Sutter Creek and Amador City and offers views of the Sutter Gold Mine and the Freemont/Grover Mine Head Frame.&amp;nbsp;Road closed down for this special event.

&amp;nbsp;

Participants will receive a custom Sport-Tek race shirt and a swag bag filled with goodies from this year&amp;rsquo;s sponsors. Overall Winners will receive a $25 Amazon Gift Card and a custom medal.&amp;nbsp; Medals will also be handed out to the
&amp;nbsp;

Online registration:&amp;nbsp; GoACRA.org/programs/bypass

&amp;nbsp;

Packet pick-up starts at 7am on Main Street, race starting at 8am.&amp;nbsp; Race day registration will be available.&amp;nbsp;
&amp;nbsp;

