Annually

2nd Saturday

in April

5:00pm - 8:00pm

&amp;nbsp;

April 08,

&amp;nbsp;



Have you ever experienced Ladies Night in Sutter Creek?&amp;nbsp; If not, it is time you came to town for an evening just for you!

&amp;nbsp;

Just what is Ladies Night? It is Sutter Creek&amp;rsquo;s way of saying &amp;ldquo;Thank You&amp;rdquo; for supporting them throughout the year. It is the merchants way of giving back to their customers (and future customers), with the opportunity to win FREE merchandise from all their wonderful stores and see what&amp;rsquo;s new.

&amp;nbsp;

What do you do for Ladies Night? Well, approximately 20 stores stay open late for you to visit. You will be welcomed with appetizers, great sales, and warm receptions from these wonderful stores. Inside each participating store you will fill out a raffle ticket and place it in the designated raffle bag to enter the FREE DRAWING for merchandise from their stores. If you happen to purchase something from that store, you will be given a SECOND raffle ticket to fill out for their drawing.

&amp;nbsp;

How do you win? At the end of the evening you will gather at the beautiful Hotel Sutter at 8:30 for the Grand Raffle Drawing.&amp;nbsp; Each bag from each store will have a raffle ticket drawn to give away the prize from that store. All in all, over $1,000 in merchandise will be given away! Winners must be present to win.

&amp;nbsp;

Don&amp;rsquo;t miss this Ladies (and Gentlemens) Night. Start at any participating store and be sure to end up at the Hotel Sutter by 8:30 for the final Raffle Drawing. We welcome the participation of the Gentleman, you may win a fantastic prize for you or your special Lady. All winners must be present to win.

&amp;nbsp;

Free child care, for kids 5 and up, at the S.C. Methodist Church on Main Street, so no excuses!

&amp;nbsp;

Sutter Creek Visitor Center

71A Main Street
Sutter Creek, CA 95685
209-267-1344
info@suttercreek.org

&amp;nbsp;

SutterCreek.org/SutterCreekLadiesNight

