Friday

May 12, 2017

Concert Starts 7 p.m.&amp;nbsp;

&amp;nbsp;


Jackson Rancheria Casino Resort welcomes Art Garfunkel to the Grand Oak Ballroom stage.

Art Garfunkel was originally revered for his Grammy-winning, chart-topping songs and albums with partner and fellow NYC native Paul Simon. &amp;nbsp;Their greatest hits collection, which includes &amp;ldquo;Mrs. Robinson,&amp;rdquo; &amp;ldquo;Scarborough Fair,&amp;rdquo; &amp;ldquo;The Sound of Silence,&amp;rdquo; &amp;ldquo;The Boxer&amp;rdquo; and &amp;ldquo;Bridge Over Troubled Water,&amp;rdquo; among others.&amp;nbsp;

&amp;nbsp;After Simon &amp;amp; Garfunkel parted ways in 1970, Garfunkel landed several major film roles, including Carnal Knowledge (opposite Jack Nicholson), Catch 22 and Nicholas Roeg&amp;rsquo;s Bad Timing/A Sensual Obsession. His solo debut Angel Clare spawned the top 10 hit &amp;ldquo;All I Know.&amp;rdquo; The 80s and 90s found Garfunkel doing what he does best: singing for an audience. &amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;Taking on the fear and vulnerability of a live show keeps you vital,&amp;rdquo; says Garfunkel, who relishes the opportunity to perform new and classic material for fans around the world. &amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;I&amp;rsquo;m a singer trying to get away with a lucky job. I try to soothe, to lift...That&amp;rsquo;s my life.&amp;rdquo;

Will Call opens at 5 p.m., doors open at 6 p.m. and the show begins at 7 p.m. Beer, food, and wine will be available for purchase.&amp;nbsp;

Tickets are on sale now starting at $40 for Dreamcatcher&amp;rsquo;s Club&amp;reg; members, available only at the Casino Cashier Cage and starting at $45 for non-Dreamcatcher&amp;rsquo;s Club&amp;reg; members, available at the Casino Cashier Cage or online at JacksonCasino.com.&amp;nbsp;


