6:00PM

&amp;nbsp;

It&amp;rsquo;s a summer tradition, TGIF Free Summer Concert Series!&amp;nbsp;

&amp;nbsp;

The 10 weekly concerts, sponsored by AmadorArts every Friday during the summer, all at a different outdoor setting, provide an experience for locals and visitors to unite around good music and picnicking, enjoyed in a variety of beautiful environments.

Being able to spread out your blanket and your chairs, eat and sip whatever you want, and invite friends and family to join you, is a real summertime joy.

&amp;nbsp;

The first 2 dates for the 2017 Concert Schedule:


June 9th- Hanford Courte, Sutter Creek

June 16th- Minnie Provis Park, Sutter Creek

To pay the musicians and other costs, the non-profit AmadorArts relies on sponsorships and on individuals when the &amp;ldquo;buckets are passed&amp;rdquo; at each concert.&amp;nbsp;

AmadorArts, the Amador County Arts Council, is a non-profit arts organization dedicated to encouraging, supporting, and promoting the arts in our schools and community.


