Annually

3rd Saturday

of August

&amp;nbsp;

8/20/2016

&amp;nbsp;

Jackson Rancheria Casino Resort and True Sportsman Club along with Gold Country Firearms host the &amp;quot;Top Cop Challenge&amp;quot;, an annual&amp;nbsp;benefit for wounded and disabled veterans. 

&amp;nbsp;

The day begins at the at the True Sportsman Club in Ione&amp;nbsp;with the &amp;ldquo;Challenge&amp;rdquo;, an individual and&amp;nbsp;two person team two gun firearms competition open to all active law enforcement.&amp;nbsp; The general public is always welcome and encouraged to come out to watch, admission-free.&amp;nbsp; Awards are presented to the first, second and third place individuals and teams.

&amp;nbsp;

The Awards Banquet following the competition is held in the Grand Oak Ballroom at the Jackson Rancheria Casino Resort, where the winners of the &amp;ldquo;Challenge&amp;rdquo; are declared.&amp;nbsp; Also a raffle, silent auction, and special drawings.&amp;nbsp;

&amp;nbsp;



&amp;nbsp;

This year, 2016,&amp;nbsp; will be Commemorating the 75th Anniversary of Pearl Harbor.&amp;nbsp; MC&amp;#39;s are Ryan Gillespie and Jim Crandall of Fox40 sports.&amp;nbsp; The theme this year is &amp;quot;South Pacific&amp;quot;, so dress in your best 1940&amp;#39;s era garb!&amp;nbsp; A great meal of prime rib and luau-style roasted pig will be served with complementary wine.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; 

&amp;nbsp;

Tickets $50/person.&amp;nbsp; Available soon online and at American River Bank, Jackson and Foothill Firearm Supply, Jackson.&amp;nbsp; All proceeds benefit wounded and disabled veterans and their families.

&amp;nbsp;

For more information contact Joe Dirickx, Chairman at (209) 223-0000 or email topcop_1@yahoo.com

&amp;nbsp;

9:00am -Gates Open to the Public

True Sportsman Club

8250 True Sportsman Drive

Ione, CA&amp;nbsp; 95640

&amp;nbsp;

5:00pm - Awards Banquet

Grand Oak Ballroom

Jackson Rancheria Casino Resort

12222 New York Ranch Rd.

Jackson, CA&amp;nbsp; 95642

&amp;nbsp;

TopCop4Vets.org

&amp;nbsp;


Founded in 2012 by Joe Dirickx of Gold Country Firearms, Top Cop&amp;nbsp;was formed as a way to raise funds for our wounded and disabled veterans. Top Cop financially supports non-profit organizations that are&amp;nbsp;not only equipped to aid our veterans recover from every type of injury from the physical to the invisible wound, but that also support, encourage and help them and their families meet essential daily needs, adjust to their new normal and work toward a brighter future.

&amp;nbsp;

