The game&amp;#39;s afoot at Baker Street West in Hein and Company Books and Vintage Goods!

&amp;nbsp;

A Mecca for all things Sherlockian including a museum-quality reproduction of Holmes&amp;#39;s and Watson&amp;#39;s sitting room, otherwise known as 221B Baker Street.

&amp;nbsp;

Beth Barnard and Linda Hein are the eccentric creators of Amador County&amp;rsquo;s Sherlockian Society, called Holmes&amp;rsquo; Hounds. What began as two long-time friends discussing their favorite books and authors, has transformed into a community of whimsical individuals with a fascination of the most re-written character in history: Sherlock Holmes.

&amp;nbsp;

Whether you are versed in every detail of Sir Arthur Conan Doyle&amp;rsquo;s life, or you simply enjoy the BBC Sherlock series, the Holmes&amp;rsquo; Hounds Sherlockian Society cordially invites you to visit 221B Baker Street and investigate for yourself.

&amp;nbsp;

Meetings are held bi-monthly, on the first Tuesday of odd-numbered months, at 6 p.m., in the upstairs of Jackson Main Street&amp;rsquo;s Hein &amp;amp; Company Bookstore.

&amp;nbsp;

