November 25th 2016

&amp;nbsp;

The day after Thanksgiving Terre Rouge and Easton Wines hold an&amp;nbsp;annual tasting of their&amp;nbsp;top syrah cuvee at the&amp;nbsp;Ascent Release Party.

&amp;nbsp;


The Terre Rouge Ascent is a limited production wine made each year from their most interesting Syrah lots from high elevation vineyard sites.

&amp;nbsp;

The wine is aged for 2 years in a special French oak barrel program. This is a special winemaker&amp;#39;s blend that is thier&amp;nbsp;top Syrah bottling.

&amp;nbsp;

Bill Easton has been making the Ascent since the 1999 vintage, garnering praise for each vintage. These wines are powerful and can cellar for at least 20 years.

&amp;nbsp;

While you taste, enjoy Jane&amp;rsquo;s Recover from Thanksgiving Soup. Bring the family and enjoy a great afternoon and if the weather is nice, play a little petanque.

&amp;nbsp;


