Delight in the charm of Jackson&amp;rsquo;s old-fashioned Christmas Delights! Santa lights the town Christmas tree at the firehouse, 6 pm Fri &amp;amp; Sat, then heads to the historic National Hotel for children&amp;rsquo;s wish lists and free photos Stroll Main Street with music, costumed characters, activities for kids Free horse-drawn carriage rides on Main Street Mrs. Claus will be at Hein &amp;amp; Co. bookstore reading holiday stories to children on&amp;nbsp;Friday. Face-painting magic with Leslie Vasquez at Davenport Properties. Festively-decorated gift shops and specialty stores will offer holiday specials to visitors
