Annually, 1st Saturday in December

10 am - 8pm

&amp;nbsp;

For more than 40 years,Calico Christmas has taken place in the historic Gold Rush town, Amador City. Calico Christmas is a perfect way to remember a childhood Christmas from an earlier time when things were relaxed and the Season was all about family celebrations! Come, join us in our town, the smallest incorporated City in all of California, where the buildings date back to the Gold Rush era of the late 1850s.

&amp;nbsp;

Fresh fir and cedar garlands festoon town, merchants have cookies, hot apple juice and other goodies for everyone. At 5:30 PM&amp;nbsp;everyone gathers in on the bridge in the center of town for the annual tree lighting and local musicians warm up the atmosphere, playing familiar carols during the evening. 

&amp;nbsp;

&amp;nbsp;

Amador City, CA

Old Highway 49




http://www.amador-city.com/index.html



info@amador-city.com

209-267-1234

