Annually

1st Saturday in December

5:00pm-8:00pm

&amp;nbsp;

Thetradition of a Scots walk in the historic community of Volcano was begun in 1982 by the Mother Lode Scots. This candlelight walk, led by pipers, starts at Volcano&amp;#39;s Armory Hall community center and proceeds to the steps of St. Bernard&amp;#39;s Catholic Church where all receive the traditional blessing in Scot&amp;#39;s Gaelic.&amp;nbsp;

&amp;nbsp;

Everyone is invited to return&amp;nbsp;to the Armory for Yuletide festivities with more musicians, dancers and performers. Enjoy be piping hot soups and stews along with homemade breads and desserts.

&amp;nbsp;

&amp;nbsp;

Armory Hall

Consolation&amp;nbsp;Street

Volcano, CA

(209) 304-3821

http://motherlodescots.com/walk.php

Chief@motherlodescots.com

