1st Sunday

December

3:00pm

&amp;nbsp;

12/4/2016

&amp;nbsp;

The 50-member Amador County Concert Band&amp;#39;s Holiday Concert is a free concert with refreshments following.

&amp;nbsp;

Established in 2001, the Amador County Community Band gathered local musicians and has since performed in Rancho Cordova, Golden Gate Park, and in 2010 represented Northern California in Washington D.C. at the National Community Concert Band Sousa Festival. In 2011 the band grew to 45 members and was renamed &amp;ldquo;Amador County Concert Band&amp;rdquo;; it is an active member of the Sacramento Valley Symphonic Band Association.

&amp;nbsp;

The band strives to perform a varied mix of musical styles. They seek to enhance the level of art in our community, to foster the importance of music in one&amp;rsquo;s own life through performance, to provide an opportunity for our talented youth to grow and perform, and to bring enjoyable and quality music to you, our friends and supporters... looking forward to seeing you at the next performance!

&amp;nbsp;

Arrive at the concert a few minutes early for best seating; music begins promptly at 3pm!

&amp;nbsp;

Community Church of Pine Grove

14045 Ponderosa Way

Pine Grove, CA&amp;nbsp; 95665

(209) 295-4305

&amp;nbsp;

www.accband.org

