&amp;nbsp;

Sutter Creek comes alive in twinkling lights, as everything from cars, mail trucks, school buses, horses, dogs, people, marching bands, baton twirlers, and more, parade down historic Sutter Creek Main Street beneath the moonlight on a crisp December evening. 

&amp;nbsp;

All the wonderful Gold Rush buildings are decked out in holiday splendor. Everyone&amp;nbsp;loves this evening of old fashioned hometown fun. Roads Close at 5:30. Parade Starts at 6:30. 


This year, we have FREE Shuttles on both ends of town to take you to Main Street to enjoy the time without the hassle of parking!&amp;nbsp; The Shuttles go from 3:00 - 6:30 and then again for an hour after the Parade is over.&amp;nbsp; We asking everyone to use this Shuttle Service to keep cars out of town that night.&amp;nbsp; .


Anyone can be in the parade, you can print out an entry form SutterCreek.org (link below), or pick one up at the Sutter Creek Visitor Center at 71A Main Street.

&amp;nbsp;

&amp;nbsp;

