Sundays

June-September

9am-12:00pm
&amp;nbsp;

Visit the Farmers Market&amp;nbsp;for fresh local produce, local crafts, live music, food and fun. Start prepping for the annual Salsa Contest. Free participation prizes for winners.


&amp;nbsp;

The market will be in the parking lot between the Jackson library on Highway 49 (530 Sutter St.) and Aces Hardware.

&amp;nbsp;

AmadorFarmersMarket.com

&amp;nbsp;

For over 100 years our Serbian-American population has celebrated on the 7th day of January, (13 days after December 25th) with a volley of rifle shots to announce that Christ Is Born.

&amp;nbsp;

There is a procession through Main St. Jackson starting approximately 12pm. The traditional volley of shots (with a police escort) in front of the National Hotel, St. Sava&amp;#39;s Church on North Main St., and St. Sava&amp;#39;s Mission on Broadway herald this unique local celebration.

&amp;nbsp;

Know that you are safe and all is well as the rifles are not loaded with live rounds. It&amp;#39;s your neighbor celebrating and keeping alive the rich traditions of the old country and wishing you every happiness this Holiday Season with great prosperity and good health in the New Year!&amp;nbsp;

&amp;nbsp;

visitjacksonca.com

info@visitjacksonca.com

209-223-1263

Wednesdays

June-September

4-7PM

&amp;nbsp;



&amp;nbsp;

Visit the Farmers Market&amp;nbsp;for fresh local produce, local crafts, live music, food and fun, especially on the last Wednesday of each month. 

&amp;nbsp;

Amador Farmer&amp;rsquo;s &amp;nbsp;Market and Upcountry Rotary Club&amp;nbsp; are collaborating to presebt an event the last Wednesday of each month including food, wine ,and local microbrew&amp;nbsp; tasting. Added bonus will be music with some of the counties best musicians. Don&amp;rsquo;t miss this great event the last Wednesday of each month through the summer.

&amp;nbsp;

Pine Grove Community Park, Hwy 88 &amp;amp; Irishtown Rd.across from the Pine Grove Town Hall.

&amp;nbsp;

&amp;nbsp;AmadorFarmersMarket.com

&amp;nbsp;

